@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.CheckBtnMenuDropDown
Summary
  Displays a button’s drop-down menu.
Description
  Call CheckMenuDropdown to manually display a button’s pop-up menu.
Return value
  Returns true and displays the menu if the speed button has an associated menu, otherwise returns
  false.
See Also
  DropDownMenu
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.Click
Summary
  Generates an OnClick event or triggers the associated action.
Description
  Calling Click generates an OnClick event, or triggers the associated action. Then, if ModalResult
  isn't equal to mrNone, it assigns the value of the button’s ModalResult property to the ModalResult
  property of its parent form. Otherwise it checks if a pop-up menu is associated with the button.
  If so, it pops up that pop-up menu.
See Also
  ButtonClick, ModalResult
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.DoubleBuffered
Summary
  Determines whether the control’s image is rendered directly to the window or painted to an in-memory
  bitmap first.
Description
  When DoubleBuffered is false, the windowed control paints itself directly to the window. When
  DoubleBuffered is true, the windowed control paints itself to an in-memory bitmap that is then used
  to paint the window. Double buffering reduces the amount of flicker when the control repaints, but
  is more memory intensive.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.Down
Summary
