----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.DropDownMenu
Summary
  Identifies a pop-up menu associated with the speed button.
Description
  Assign a value to DropDownMenu to make a menu appear when the button is pressed. (To display the
  menu programmatically, call the speed button’s Click or ButtonClickmethod.) If the menu’s
  AutoPopup property is set to true, the menu appears automatically. If AutoPopup is false,
  display the menu by calling the menu’s Popup method in the speed button’s OnClick event handler.
See Also
  Click, MarkDropDown, MenuPosition
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.Flat
Summary
  Determines whether the button has a 3D border that provides a raised or lowered look.
Description
  See Delphi help at TSpeedButton.Flat for more info.
See Also
  GrayedInactive
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.GrayedInactive
Summary
  Indicates whether to display the image of the button grayed when the button is inactive.
Description
  Set GrayedInactive to true to render the image of the button grayed, when the button is
  <LINK TJvCustomSpeedButton.Flat,flat> and the mouse pointer is not on the button (i.e., the button
  is inactive)
See Also
  Flat, GrayNewStyle
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.GrayNewStyle
Summary
  Specifies the graying style of the image when the button is not enabled.
Description
  Set GrayNewStyle to false to render the image of a disabled button the same way as TSpeedButton does.
  Set GrayNewStyle to true to render the image of a disabled button the same way as TImageList does.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.GroupIndex
Summary
