Description
  See Delphi help at TSpeedButton.GroupIndex for more info.
See Also
  AllowAllUp, <LINK Down>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.HotTrack
Summary
  Specifies whether the button is highlighted when the mouse passes over it.
Description
  Set HotTrack to true to provide visual feedback about which item is under the mouse; the font
  specified by HotTrackFont is used for the button text. When HotTrack is false, there is no visual
  feedback when the mouse passes over the button.
See Also
  TJvImageSpeedButton.HotTrackImageIndex, TJvSpeedButton.HotTrackGlyph, HotTrackFont, OnMouseEnter,
  OnMouseLeave
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.HotTrackFont
Summary
  Specifies the font used when the mouse passes over the button and HotTrack is true.
Description
  When the mouse passes over the button and HotTrack is set to true, HotTrackFont is used as the font
  for the button text.
  To change to a new font, specify a new TFont object. To modify a font, change the value of the
  Charset, Color, Height, Name, Pitch, Size, or Style of the TFont object.
See Also
  TJvImageSpeedButton.HotTrackImageIndex, TJvSpeedButton.HotTrackGlyph, HotTrack
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.HotTrackFontOptions
Summary
  Specifies how changes to the Font affects HotTrackFont.
Description
  HotTrackFontOptions defines a set of options that controls how changes to the Font property affects
  the HotTrackFont object. For example, when HotTrackFontOptions includes hoPreserveColor, all property
  changes in Font are copied to HotTrackFont except Color changes.
  
  Note that hoFollowFont must be included for any properties to be copied at all.
  
  To implement the HotTrackFontOptions property in a new control, you should perform the following steps:
    * Add JvTypes and JvJVCLUtils to the uses clause of the control's unit.
    * Add a HotTrackFontOptions property of type TJvTrackFontOptions to the control. Set its default value
      to be DefaultTrackFontOptions (defined in JvTypes).
    * Set the default value in the constructor.
    * Add a handler for the CM_FONTCHANGED message. Add a call to UpdateTrackFont (defined in JvJVCLUtils)
      after calling inherited.
    * Add a call to UpdateTrackFont in SetHotTrackFontOptions
See Also
  HotTrack, HotTrackFont
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.InitPause
Summary
  Determines the amount of time, in milliseconds, that passes before the button calls Click for the
  first time, when pressed.
Description
  Use InitPause to set the amount of time, in milliseconds, that passes before the button
  calls Click <i>for the first time</i>, when pressed.

  Property RepeatInterval determines the amount of time, in milliseconds, that passes before the
  button calls Click <i>again</i>, when pressed.
Note
  AllowTimer must be set to true.
See Also
  AllowTimer, RepeatInterval
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.IsDragging
Summary
  Indicates whether the user left-clicked the button and is still holding the mouse button down.
Description
  Read IsDragging to determine whether the user is 'dragging' the button, ie
  the user left-clicked on the speed button and is still holding the mouse button down.
See Also
  <LINK Down>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.Layout
Summary
  Specifies where the image appears on the button.
Description
  Layout indicates whether the text appears on the left of the button (blGlyphLeft), the right of the
  button (blGlyphRight), the top (blGlyphTop) or the bottom (blGlyphBottom).
See Also
  Margin
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.Margin
Summary
  Specifies the number of pixels between the edge of the image (specified in the Glyph property) and
  the edge of the button.
Description
  The margin is the space between the image edge and the button edge. The format of the edges depends
  on the layout of the image and text (specified in the Layout property). For example, if Layout is
  blGlyphLeft, the margin appears between the left edge of the image and the left edge of the button.
  If Margin is 3, three pixels separate the image and the button edges. If Margin is 0, there is no
  space between the image and the button edges.

  If Margin is -1 (the default value), the image and text (specified in the Caption property) are centered.
  The number of pixels between the image and button edge is equal to the number of pixels between the
  opposite edge of the button and the text.
See Also
  Spacing
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.MarkDropDown
Summary
  Specifies whether the button displays a downward-pointing arrow.
Description
  Use MarkDropDown to get or set whether the button displays a downward-pointing arrow. MarkDropDown
  is typically set to true when a pop-up menu is associated with the speed button (via property
  DropDownMenu)
See Also
  DropDownMenu, MenuPosition
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.MenuPosition
Summary
  Specifies the position where the pop-up menu will appear.
Description
  Use MenuPosition to set the position where the pop-up menu will appear. Use property DropDownMenu
  to associate a pop-up menu with the speed button.
See Also
  DropDownMenu, MarkDropDown
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.ModalResult
Summary
  Determines whether and how the button closes its (modal) parent form.
Description
  Setting the button’s ModalResult property is an easy way to make clicking the button close
  a modal form. When a button is clicked, the ModalResult property of its parent form is set to the
  same value as the button’s ModalResult property.

  For example, if a dialog box has OK and Cancel buttons, their ModalResult properties could be set
  at design time to mrOk and mrCancel, respectively. At runtime, clicking the OK button then changes
  the dialog’s ModalResult property to mrOk, and clicking the Cancel button changes the dialog’s
  ModalResult property to mrCancel. Unless further processing is required, no OnClick event handlers
  are required for the buttons.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.RepeatInterval
Summary
  Determines the amount of time, in milliseconds, that passes before the button calls Click again,
  when pressed.
Description
  Use RepeatInterval to set the amount of time, in milliseconds, that passes before the button calls
  Click <i>again</i>, when pressed.

  Property InitPause determines the amount of time, in milliseconds, that passes before the button
  calls Click <i>for the first time</i>, when pressed.
Note
  AllowTimer must be set to true.
See Also
  AllowTimer, InitPause
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.Spacing
Summary
  Determines where the image and text appear on a speed button.
Description
  See Delphi help at TSpeedButton.Spacing for more info.
See Also
  Layout, Margin
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.Style
Summary
  Determines the appearance of a button.
Description
  Style indicates whether the speed button uses the modern button look, or reflects the look of
  a 16-bit Windows pushbutton.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.Transparent
Summary
  Specifies whether the background of the button is transparent.
Description
  Use Transparent to specify whether the background of the button is transparent.
See Also
  Flat
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.UpdateTracking
Summary
  Updates the MouseInControl property.
Description
  UpdateTracking is used internally by the speed button to resync the MouseInControl property.
See Also
  MouseInControl
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomSpeedButton.WordWrap
Summary
  Specifies whether the button text wraps to fit the width of the control.
Description
  Set WordWrap to true to allow the speed button to display multiple line of text. When WordWrap is true,
  text that is too wide for the control wraps at the right margin.

  Set WordWrap to false to limit the button to a single line. When WordWrap is false, text that is too
  wide for the button appears truncated.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
