Summary
  Specifies the bitmap that appears on the speed button.
Description
  See Delphi help at TSpeedButton.Glyph for more info.
See Also
  HotTrackGlyph, NumGlyphs
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSpeedButton.HotTrackGlyph
Summary
  Specifies the bitmap that appears on the speed button when the mouse pointer passes over the button.
Description
  See Delphi help at TSpeedButton.Glyph for more info.
See Also
  Glyph, NumGlyphs
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSpeedButton.NumGlyphs
Summary
  Specifies the number of images included in the Glyph property.
Description
  Set NumGlyphs to the number of images provided by the bitmap assigned to the Glyph property. All
  images must be the same size and next to each other in a row. Unlike TSpeedbutton, the Glyph
  property can provide up to five images (one image more, for the inactive state, ie when the
  button is flat and and the mouse pointer is not on the button).
See Also
  Glyph, HotTrackGlyph
